  "text": "Purification and Characterization of PEG-Grafted NPs. The NPs were gel-filtrated through a hand-packed 25 cm/2.5 cm Sephadex G75 column in pure water using just hydrostatic pressure to ensure removal of unbound excess ligands. The eluate was split into fractions, which were analyzed in terms of grafting density. The fractions with a grafting density of 3.5 chains/nm 2 as determined by TGA, displaying the highest colloidal stability, [CITATION_1] were selected for all further experiments.",
